snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 11/19 - 11/23
snippet.description:
#Mantle4Mantle submissions must be posted to our twitter, facebook or e-mail by December 1st! http://5secondfilms.com/mantle

How was your Thanksgiving? Ours rocked.

snippet.title: 5SF BTS - More Wine Glasses
snippet.description: Watch the 5sf first (http://youtu.be/HkOIm6sCI9E) if you haven't already, then watch these numerous outtakes!

snippet.title: New Restaurant Old Couple
snippet.description: They base their whole schedule around when new, oddly named restaurants are opening, and when they're busy screwing each other's friends and relatives. It's their favorite activity to do together/decidedly not together.

snippet.title: The First Thanksgiving
snippet.description: Thanksjesus is keen to point out white devils of all shapes and sizes, as well as Dust Devils, dirt devils, and deviled eggs. If you ever catch him accidentally playing devil's advocate on an issue, you get to go to ThanksHeaven for free. It's in the Bible.

snippet.title: People Saying Important Things Into Wine Glasses
snippet.description: Saying important things sucks and drinking wine kicks ass. The solution, ladies and gentlemen, is obvimhmmmrbbbllbllbrmmblr.

snippet.title: Old Fashioned Stalker
snippet.description: He even takes time to cut individual letters out of magazines to spell things like "I WILL STRING YOUR LONG INTESTINE AROUND YOUR MAILBOX." What a thoughtful guy, right? I mean, who even reads magazines anymore?

snippet.title: Manscaping
snippet.description: Putting the flamingo on the left is a good idea, as the right side is already taken up by a patch of gardenias, a garden gnome, two wrinkly balls, a rose bush and a big honkin' cock.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week 11/12 - 11/17
snippet.description: Cassidy brings da ruckus, The Gang realize they're terrible spellers, but the Mantle 4 Mantle contest continues anyway!

snippet.title: 5SF BTS - How to Look Like You've Partied Hard
snippet.description: Andrew WK shows Brian how to apply simple bathroom items like soap, water and staring (note: not an actual bathroom item) to look like he's spent a night partying hard! Your shirt may get wet, but the results will be worth it.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #212
snippet.description: Banished because of a horrible tramp stamp tattoo a drunk must now fight his nocturnal emissions in Colorado.

snippet.title: Meanwhile In Colorado...
snippet.description: See, the problem here is that Prop 472B passed as well, which states that aggro Colorado cops, denied the chance to bust in some stoner hippie heads, have free reign to travel to other states and commit manslaughter or even murder if they so choose. I would suggest we all flee the country, except the fine print in 472B says they legally have no national jurisdiction.

snippet.title: Nocturnal Emissions
snippet.description: Curiously enough, it was just a dream about dumping a bunch of Fritos into a salad bowl and drizzling maple syrup over it. Sure, there were firemen hooking up a hose to a fire hydrant, but they were outside the kitchen window and practically incidental to the main Fritos narrative of the dream.

snippet.title: Never Gonna Drink Again
snippet.description: He's a great party wingman until your liquor starts to taste like water. Then he becomes something else entirely.

snippet.title: Tramp Stamp
snippet.description: Her friends tried to stop her from getting more, but it was too late: She was addicted. The next day, she breezed into a sketchy ink parlor in Chinatown, asking to get the Chinese symbol for "I'm dissatisfied with where I've ended up in life and I'm trying to reclaim control by marking up my body with things I'll regret mere months from now." Since that was precisely what the tattoo artist was going to draw on her as a prank, he felt he had no choice but to instead ink the symbol for "Strength." She never knew the difference anyway.

snippet.title: Banishment
snippet.description: The town of Equalrightstria loves a good banishing at dawn, and the town crier is always present to cup an ear towards the fields, just to make sure there isn't any attempt at pathos on the part of the accused. At 11 AM there are scones, mead and a hearty discussion on women's studies for all.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #211
snippet.description: While making bacon in the voting booth a depressed stalker over shared his scalding grease and it went viral all over his junk.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 11/5 - 11/9
snippet.description:
Our Mantle 4 Mantle contest is ON!! Win Maria's 5sf painting of Satan and Hypnotic Southern General by 1) Making your own piece of 5sf fan art that we can hang on our mantle, 2) taking a picture of it and tweeting us a picture at twitter.com/5sf (with the hashtag #Mantle4Mantle, then 3) if you're selected to be in our Top 10 submissions, and the fans on Facebook vote yours to the top...then you send us your artwork (shipping paid for) and we'll send you ours!!

The due date to send us your entries via twitter is December 1st! They must be sent to us by the end of that day, with the hashtag #Mantle4Mantle!

Also, a shoutout is due towards the good people at the r/InternetAMA subreddit! We had a great time answering all your questions, and should the occasion ever arise again when people feel they truly haven't asked us everything they want to, we'd be obliged!

snippet.title: 5SF Outtakes 11/5 - 11/9
snippet.description: Outtakes from last week's 5sfs! Hope you like 'em!

snippet.title: Viral Video
snippet.description: "Dying Kid" eventually hit #1 on iTunes for 12 solid weeks, even though it was just a dialysis machine beep set to a David Guetta beat. He was invited to come onto Jimmy Fallon but he was dead. And Gawker ran articles on it for weeks, generating thousands of comments, but you can't tell who's replying to who on that site so it was exhausting to search through.

snippet.title: The Oversharer
snippet.description:
We are doing an AMA right now on Reddit Ask Us Anything! http://tinyurl.com/aatnjwz

He's been kicked out of numerous coffee shops, bars and restaurants, yet he keeps coming back to stream 40gb of porn at any given minute on their public wi-fi for customers. You can withhold the password from him. He's still going to know it's "Passw0rd."

snippet.title: Say Anything Louder
snippet.description: Peter Gabriel has a pretty obscure B-Side called "Attention Mother: Your Daughter is Upstairs Making Out With My Mortal Enemy, The Jock" from the 80′s, but it's really hard to locate a tape of it in a record store for anything less than $1200.

snippet.title: New Voting Method
snippet.description: There was a lot of controversy in the media that this new method was prejudiced against non-buff minorities and elderly folk, but screw it, they should just do more crossfit if they're so upset about voting for the wrong guy, bros.

snippet.title: The Dangers of Makin' Bacon
snippet.description: The Dangers of Makin' Fakin' Bacon usually entail two drunk girls making out, but we didn't really have the budget for that one.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #210 Halloween Week
snippet.description: 5secondfilms Halloween Week!!!

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 10/29 - 11/2
snippet.description:
Enter "50K" in the promo code box at store.5secondfilms.com to receive 10% off any item! Including our super cool new posters!!

Let's all have tea together sometime.

snippet.title: What Were You...
snippet.description: Frankie and Cinnamon would see each other three more times during the course of Frankie's annual Vegas trips with his golfing buddies. By the third time, Frankie had broken a leg trying to jump four floors into the hot tub of the MGM Grand, and wouldn't ya know it, it was Dr. Cinnamon who reset his bones in the ER. Frankie then sued for medical malpractice on a paperwork technicality and Cinnamon was back to hooking in no time.

snippet.title: A Real Found Footage Horror Movie
snippet.description: Ah, but putting down the camera precludes you from spawning a $600 million blockbuster horror franchise, with a new installment every October. Should your friends die, or should you go broke trying to be a filmmaker? I think your friends would want you to be happy and successful.

snippet.title: The Early Bird Killer
snippet.description: Ever since he switched to decaf, cut out heavy food after 6 PM, and started using piano wire to slice his victims' throats, he's really increased his productivity. In fact, he's behind you right now.

snippet.title: The Dorian Gray Diet
snippet.description: Satanic magical Faustian-bargain horrifying twist-ending diet fads never work. Just eat less, move more and supplement with the occasional cursed talisman.

snippet.title: Say His Name Three Times
snippet.description: The more people who believe in his terrifying legend, the more amped he gets. Or it could just be all the sugary candy he steals from your trick-or-treater buckets by the front door. It could totally be that.

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 10/22 -10/26
snippet.description:
POSTERS!! http://store.5secondfilms.com

And we're 262 followers away from hitting 50K on Twitter! Help us out if you don't follow us already! twitter.com/5sf

We celebrate our 4-year-anniversary this week by bringing back Chartio, singing a few 90's hits, re-enacting the end of a classic children's film about a killer whale, and the words "Ribbed Strap-On" are uttered in slow-motion.

We could've just not done a CotW this week, due to how drunk we were and how messy our house was from the Halloween party, but screw it: WE CARE ABOUT OUR FANS DAMMIT.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #209
snippet.description: Misdialing on her time traveling phone a masseuse accidentally tells a homeless man in the future that his once successful robot coworker design has been fired because of a glitch in its mapping system, but it was opposite day so he didn't give no shit.

snippet.title: Siri-ous Help
snippet.description: Apple Maps does a great, great, GREAT job of finding long-lost and even deceased dads. To the point that Apple CEO Tim Cook, when presented with this information, seriously considered just changing the name of the app to Apple Dads.

snippet.title: Bentley the Break Room Robot
snippet.description: He's programmed to boost company morale (and store all of the server room's metadata), but instead he's boosting all the good snacks and replacing the metadata with useless pop culture conversations.

snippet.title: Opposite Day
snippet.description: They later suffered massive head trauma when they rode bikes backwards on the 10 West Interstate heading East, pedaling with their hands and holding their breath. The doctor declared them dead, shook their feet hello and released them from the McDonald's parking lot across the street from the hospital.

snippet.title: Happy Ending
snippet.description: Somedays she really phones it in at the end, and just starts picking random points in "Love Actually" to describe -- forgetting, as always, that "Love Actually" ends in the graphic disembowelment of Colin Firth with Hugh Grant videotaping it.

snippet.title: Time Travel Phone
snippet.description: Seeing as how each phone call sets you back $15,000, Mark has reason to be angry with his past self. Sadly, the anger creates a cycle of phone bills that can seemingly never be broken.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week in Review #208
snippet.description: Felix Baumgartner's stupidest nephew, Clay--A TRUE AMERICAN--died in that jump. But Paul Ryan has a plan for him! Yes he does! One night stands and all the BOOTY a pirate could ask for!!! (this message brought to you by the Pigeon Party of the United Kingdom).

snippet.title: 5sf's Comments of the Week - 10/15 - 10/19
snippet.description:
To celebrate our upcoming 4 year anniversary, go to store.5secondfilms.com and save 20% on shot glasses and 5sf logo T-shirts when you enter "4YEARS" in the promo code box!

Also, we discuss many things this week. That happens as well.

snippet.title: Revenge on the Pigeons
snippet.description: Three days later, the pigeons hobbled across the lawn to their beat-up 1995 Toyota Celica. It had a log of human feces right on top of the left windshield wiper. There was much angry feather-ruffling.

snippet.title: Captain's Order
snippet.description: The crew figured something was up when Glass Eye Pete sneezed too hard, shooting his glass eye into the ocean, causing the captain to leap overboard and dog paddle 30 yards out to retrieve it. Even Pete could barely muster a "yarr, thank ye," as it became pretty evident the captain wanted him to do it again.

snippet.title: One Night Stand
snippet.description: A Low-Five is reserved only in the most dire of circumstances. But there's hope; at least she didn't yank it away from her friend at the last second for being "too slow." Then that would mean certain death.

snippet.title: Paul Ryan's Workout Plan For America
snippet.description: Did you see how hard Paulie's been blasting his pectorals? Check the striations on those pumped-up calves! Bro's fitness plans for the country are SOUND, dude! Just the thing to lead us out of this long national nightmare of commie rowing exercises!

snippet.title: Red Bull's Stratos Test Jump #1
snippet.description: For a while there during the early stages, Red Bull had confused "Fund NASA in order to successfully complete a huge jump" with "Silly Flugtag shenanigans doomed to failure." It cost 473 men their lives. Their families were given a very comprehensive gag order, along with a free case of Sugar Free Red Bull every week for the rest of their lives.

snippet.title: 5SF Comments of the Week 10/7 - 10/12
snippet.description: This time on CotW: A buncha randos you've never ever seen before join us to talk about bears and other shit! More honorable mentions, pointless and dis-orienting zooms, stupid post FX, drunk shouting, great steel guitar music, then some violin music, more shouting about Jon Salmon, Michael burns Ben for no reason, he will suffer for it later, and THINGS BROUGHT TO YOU BY HONEYLARD, then we talk about Brian and his sex life for the better part of like...2 minutes. Deal with it.

snippet.title: 5secondfilms Week In Review #207
snippet.description: A gym teacher's germophobia gets in the way of the romantic camping trip he was planning with his motorcycle casting director.

snippet.title: Kelsey's Big Hollywood Break
snippet.description: If all these Kelseys teamed up, they could form some sort of Voltron-Kelsey with each girl operating a different limb, and thus contribute to the physicality of the audition with their own unique kicking, punching and laser-blasting skills. But no, there's no such thing as sisterhood in the waiting room.

snippet.title: Lugnuts
snippet.description: He was so excited about acquiring this new authority figure in his life, he even got his work to put on a "Take Our Dads to Work Day," which wound up accidentally revealing how many gay dads his co-workers had.

snippet.title: Roughing It
snippet.description: You can delete your history, but you might wind up burning the whole forest down.

snippet.title: Germaphobe's Dilemma
snippet.description: Anti-venom actually forms a chemical compound with dirt to create Mountain Dew Baja Blast, which they can enjoy after he sucks the venom out.
